Key Match Events: Netherlands defeated Namibia on October 18, 2022, in a nervy game.
Bas de Leede was adjudged the man of the match for his two wickets and his fighting 30 off 30 balls.
Openers Vikramjeet Singh and Max O'Dowd gave a good start to the Netherlands team.
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands captain Scott Edwards expressed that the fate of their qualification was well and truly in their hands.
Bas de Leede mentioned that the self-belief has always been there and it's nice to get two tight games go their way.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netherlands have won back-to-back games against UAE and Namibia.
The win places Netherlands at the very top of their group.
